that happens immediately in the period of receipt of the stimulus a “splurge.” This
splurge behavior is common across households and independent of their liquid wealth
holdings. As such, it is consistent with the empirical finding that even households with
high liquid wealth have high MPCs in the first quarter.2 The evidence of front-loading
