The specific exercise we carry out in this section, is to show that our model can
account well for the results of Fagereng, Holm, and Natvik (2021), who study the effect of
lottery winnings in Norway on consumption using millions of records from the Norwegian
population registry. We calibrate our model to reflect the Norwegian economy and, using
